<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.002/79: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Abbott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-02-06T22:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1924—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 6—9:40
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>35. Legation’s 33 February 5, 4 p.m. New Cabinet under the Presidency of
                            Cafandaris, who has taken Ministry of Foreign Affairs, took oath
                            today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Abbott</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>